
C:\dev\GeoDMS_2026>setlocal

C:\dev\GeoDMS_2026>REM BuildSignAndCreateSetupLinux.bat 

C:\dev\GeoDMS_2026>REM Builds the linux (l) flavor of GeoDMS via WSL2 (CMake), then runs 

C:\dev\GeoDMS_2026>REM nsi/CreateLinuxSetup.sh to package + sign, then optionally installs the 

C:\dev\GeoDMS_2026>REM .deb via dpkg inside WSL so it can be tested via: 

C:\dev\GeoDMS_2026>REM    python full.py -version <ver>l 

C:\dev\GeoDMS_2026>REM (the linux flavor of full.py invokes the binary via `wsl --` — see 

C:\dev\GeoDMS_2026>REM the linux-handling extension in full.py's _resolve_local_build). 

C:\dev\GeoDMS_2026>REM

C:\dev\GeoDMS_2026>REM Sister script of BuildSignAndCreateSetup.bat (m, msbuild) and 

C:\dev\GeoDMS_2026>REM BuildSignAndCreateSetupCmake.bat (c, cmake). 

C:\dev\GeoDMS_2026>REM

C:\dev\GeoDMS_2026>REM Prereqs: 

C:\dev\GeoDMS_2026>REM   - WSL2 with Ubuntu 24.04 (or similar) installed 

C:\dev\GeoDMS_2026>REM   - cmake, ninja, gcc-13, vcpkg available inside WSL 

C:\dev\GeoDMS_2026>REM   - Linux build tree: build/linux-x64-release/  (configured separately) 

C:\dev\GeoDMS_2026>REM   - dpkg-deb available in WSL (for .deb creation) 

C:\dev\GeoDMS_2026>REM

C:\dev\GeoDMS_2026>REM Run from the repo root:  C:\dev\GeoDMS_2026>BuildSignAndCreateSetupLinux.bat 

C:\dev\GeoDMS_2026>cls

C:\dev\GeoDMS_2026>REM Version comes from nsi\GeoDmsVersion.cmd (shared with the msbuild + cmake 

